'''Senegambia and Niger''' was a short-lived administrative unit of the  possessions in , formed in  and reorganized in  into .
Despite its brief existence, the French government still managed to issue s for the administrative unit, in the form of a version of its , inscribed "SENEGAMBIE / ET NIGER". The set consisted of 13 values, from 1  to 1 . For s today, the price ranges from 1 US$ for the low values and up for 40 US$ for the 1-franc value.